ZH: 这只小猫贪吃。
EN: This little cat is greedy.

ZH: 他贪婪地抢走了我的玩具。
EN: He greedily snatched away my toy.

ZH: 她贪心地想要更多。
EN: She greedily wanted more.

ZH: 小偷贪心地窃取了所有的钱。
EN: The thief greedily stole all the money.

ZH: 他们贪图金钱和名利。
EN: They covet money and fame.

ZH: 贪赃枉法是不道德的。
EN: Corruption is immoral.

ZH: 贪图利益会导致坏事发生。
EN: Greed for profit can lead to bad things happening.

ZH: 贪心的举动会导致失败。
EN: Greedy actions will lead to failure.

ZH: 贪心的人永远不会满足。
EN: Greedy people will never be satisfied.

ZH: 他贪污了公款。
EN: He embezzled public funds.

ZH: 贪人不得志。
EN: The greedy will not succeed.

ZH: 贪念害人。
EN: Greed harms people.

ZH: 贪图他人之财是不道德的。
EN: Coveting the wealth of others is immoral.

ZH: 贪图权力会导致腐败。
EN: Coveting power can lead to corruption.

ZH: 他因为贪心而丧失了朋友。
EN: He lost his friends because of his greed.

ZH: 贪恋荣华富贵是愚蠢的。
EN: It is foolish to covet wealth and power.

ZH: 贪心的人很容易陷入困境。
EN: Greedy people are easily trapped in difficulties.

ZH: 贪不悔改是罪恶。
EN: Greed without repentance is sinful.

ZH: 贪欲是人类的大敌。
EN: Greed is a great enemy of humanity.

ZH: 贪欲是许多问题的根源。
EN: Greed is the root of many problems.
